To install:

1. run install on setup script:

python setup.py install

2. copy app package ('parleys_creek_management' directory) to 'ckanapp' directory in the Tethys Apps plugin source

3. create a user and database for the app

4. Modify configuration file (app.ini)

Example app.ini:

[database]
sqlalchemy_url = postgresql://pcmt:pcmt_pass@localhost:5432/pcmt

[dataset]
ckan_dataset_name = parleys-creek-management-app-datasets

The ckan_dataset_name parameter is optional. It is used to name the dataset in CKAN that is used
to store the app results. If this parameter is not provided, the default will be used:
parleys-creek-management-app-datasets. The sqlalchemy_url is required and it needs to point to a
database that has been initialized using the init_db script that comes with the app.

5. Run init_db.py that is located in the lib directory of the app source code

python init_db.py
